ing <br>note that on the bottom of the raid calandar is the dont abuse the calandar system by multi booking things etc.. or using different peoples names and still doing a guild raid this is based on the honor system if you have no HONOR it will become apparent, if your guild continually overbooks then it will become apparent that your guild does NOT value honor and decency and therefore honesty and truth are probably a casualty also (in that guild).<br><br>----------------------------------------------------------<br>So what I have found so far is that there might be  a misundertanding of the way the Calandar works, Bish explained it well in his reply but thats not written out on the calandar.<br><br>I am one to give the benefit of the doubt, that those that are overbooked believe its 3 current reservations per month or 30 days or whatever. <br><br>I hope that this post will show them that its not setup that way becuase if it were lets do the math (100 guilds (at the moment) 3 raids each per month in 30 days with 3 planes to go to.  <br><br>90 raids available per month which leaves us short 210 scheduled dates.<br><br>when the guild level increases not to mention the amount of open and invite raids from NON-GUILDED we are way short with this assumption of how the calandar works.<br><br>I urge everyone to consider the system and reserve accordingly, if you are currently overbooked and its a mistake due to misunderstanding or miscommunication then I urge you to email bish and have him remove the overbooked dates.<br><br>the following is a list of guilds and players that are overbooked as of this time:<br><br>Chaotic Justice:  9-20/9-25/10-1/10-2/-10-3<br>Colleague of Sanctuary: 9-22/9-26/10-6/10-13/10-14<br>Praxiums: 10-12/10-26/9-25/9-30/11-3/11-17<br>Blood Alliance: 11-23/11-24/11-25/10-19/10-26/9-22/9-28<br>Ginthal : 10-1/10-2/10-3/10-9<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><sp